[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] List the expected variants in the new behavior.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] pass if the variant in the new behavior is met.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] This shows that new code is actually needed for the desired feature.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] It rules out the possibility that the new test is flawed and will always pass.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] No code should be added beyond the tested functionality.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] If any fail, fix failing tests with minimal changes until all pass.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] In particular, hard-coded test data should be removed from the production code.
