[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] Exercising TDD on large systems requires a modular architecture, defined components with published interfaces, and disciplined system layering with maximization of platform independence.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] These proven practices yield increased testability and facilitate the application of build and test automation.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] Complex systems require an architecture that meets a range of requirements.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] A key subset of these requirements includes support for the complete and effective testing of the system.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] Effective modular design yields components that share traits essential for effective TDD.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] A key technique for building effective modular architecture is Scenario Modeling where a set of sequence charts is constructed, each one focusing on a single system-level execution scenario.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] The Scenario Model provides an excellent vehicle for creating the strategy of interactions between components in response to a specific stimulus.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] Each of these Scenario Models serves as a rich set of requirements for the services or functions that a component must provide, and it also dictates the order in which these components and services interact together.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] Scenario modeling can greatly facilitate the construction of TDD tests for a complex system.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] In a larger system, the impact of poor component quality is magnified by the complexity of interactions.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] This magnification makes the benefits of TDD accrue even faster in the context of larger projects.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] However, the complexity of the total population of tests can become a problem in itself, eroding potential gains.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] It sounds simple, but a key initial step is to recognize that test code is also important software and should be produced and maintained with the same rigor as the production code.
[src:catch2-cpp-lib/test-driven-development] Creating and managing the architecture of test software within a complex system is just as important as the core product architecture.
